(198, 'E&E2.13', 'Incapacity Benefit (HISTORIC)\nFirst order fiscal benefit from a workless claimant entering work', '8160.00', 2010, '(DWP 2011) Co-Design Interim Report (Annex A) p29', 'http://www.dwp.gov.uk/publications/policy-publications/worklessness-codesign.shtml', 'High', 'DWP note: whilst the data are based upon getting the claimant into work for an entire year, internal analysis shows that at the national level around 75% of IB claimants stay off benefit for twelve months or more.  Data take into account the effect of in-work tax credits (which off-set some of the benefit savings), and represent the ''average'' claimant, not those in disadvantaged groups such as ethnic minorities and older people (the cost of getting some groups into employment is likely to be greater than the average cost).', 3, 10, 4, 39, 21, NULL),
