(497, 'CR1.0', 'Anti-social behaviour\nfurther action necessary\n(cost of dealing with incident)', '500.00', 2002, 'The Economic and Social Costs of Anti-Social Behaviour: a review'' (London School of Economics and Political Science, 2003), p.43', 'http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20100405140447/http:/asb.homeoffice.gov.uk/uploadedFiles/Members_site/Documents_and_images/About_ASB_general/EconSocialCostASB_0142.pdf', 'Low', 'Source gives a (non-updated) cost range from £100 - £1,000 for ASB incidents of this kind (ranging from a call-out together with some remedial action, to significant mediation/remediation; falling short of issuing an ASBO, as not used very often).  An approximate average cost of £500 has been selected, and updated to account for inflation.  Note age of data.  Home Office suggest a Red RAG assessment due to the age of data and robustness of methodology.  However, there is no more recent national research in this area', 1, 8, 12, NULL, 37, NULL),
(498, 'CR1.1', 'Anti-social behaviour\nno further action taken\n(simple police reporting of incident)', '35.00', 2002, 'The Economic and Social Costs of Anti-Social Behaviour: a review'' (London School of Economics and Political Science, 2003), p.43', 'http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20100405140447/http:/asb.homeoffice.gov.uk/uploadedFiles/Members_site/Documents_and_images/About_ASB_general/EconSocialCostASB_0142.pdf', 'Low', 'Source gives a (non-updated) cost range from £20-£50 for ASB incidents of this kind - mid-point cost value (£35) has been selected, and updated to account for inflation.  Note age of data.  Home Office suggest a Red RAG assessment due to the age of data and robustness of methodology.  However, there is no more recent national research in this area', 1, 8, 12, NULL, 37, NULL),
(499, 'CR1.2', 'Anti-social behaviour\nwarning letter delivered', '66.00', 2006, 'National Audit Office (2006) Tackling Anti-Social Behaviour p24 Fig13', 'http://www.nao.org.uk/publications/0607/tackling_anti-social_behaviour.aspx', 'Medium', 'Warning letters are generally used for relatively minor acts of anti-social behaviour and are unlikely to be effective for more serious incidents.', 1, 8, 8, 38, 6, NULL),
(500, 'CR1.5', 'Acceptable Behaviour Contract issued', '230.00', 2006, 'National Audit Office (2006) Tackling Anti-Social Behaviour p24 Fig13', 'http://www.nao.org.uk/publications/0607/tackling_anti-social_behaviour.aspx', 'Medium', 'Note age of data.  Based on seminars in 12 local areas involving practitioners from a range of agencies including the police and local authorities. The cost does not include the cost of other support services which may be provided in conjunction with the intervention e.g. youth projects or drug rehabilitation schemes, nor does it include the cost of policing the intervention. Court costs are included but legal aid costs are not.', 1, 8, 2, 47, 1, NULL),
(501, 'CR1.6', 'Neighbourhood dispute: Local Authority mediation - average costs', '105.00', 2003, 'Scottish Executive (2003): The role of mediation in tackling neighbourhood disputes and anti-social behaviour', 'http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Resource/Doc/47176/0029635.pdf', 'Medium', 'Based on 100 case studies in 2003. Calculated net costs in the present study, that is, the costs of staff time and travel costs that can directly be attributed to cases. These net costs exclude\norganisational overheads, that is, building and office costs, staff training, and central services such as personnel.', 1, 8, 8, NULL, 6, NULL),
(502, 'CR1.6.1', 'Neighbourhood dispute: Local Authority mediation - Verbal abuse', '197.00', 2003, 'Scottish Executive (2003): The role of mediation in tackling neighbourhood disputes and anti-social behaviour', 'http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Resource/Doc/47176/0029635.pdf', 'Medium', 'Based on 100 case studies in 2003. Calculated net costs in the present study, that is, the costs of staff time and travel costs that can directly be attributed to cases. These net costs exclude\norganisational overheads, that is, building and office costs, staff training, and central services such as personnel.', 1, 8, 8, NULL, 6, 501),
(503, 'CR1.6.2', 'Neighbourhood dispute: Local Authority mediation - Noise (including element of verbal abuse)', '107.00', 2003, 'Scottish Executive (2003): The role of mediation in tackling neighbourhood disputes and anti-social behaviour', 'http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Resource/Doc/47176/0029635.pdf', 'Medium', 'Based on 100 case studies in 2003. Calculated net costs in the present study, that is, the costs of staff time and travel costs that can directly be attributed to cases. These net costs exclude\norganisational overheads, that is, building and office costs, staff training, and central services such as personnel.', 1, 8, 8, NULL, 6, 501),
